5000|$|The Under Secretary also <b>advises</b> <b>the</b> Secretary on the Department's {{educational}} and training activities. Other aspects include <b>advising</b> <b>the</b> Secretary on the coordinating and planning of research activities, <b>advising</b> <b>the</b> Secretary on financial assistance for research activities, and carrying out additional duties {{assigned by the}} Secretary, including supervising and supporting the lower-ranking Assistant Secretaries' research activities. In {{the words of the}} Act, the Under Secretary is required to have [...] "extensive background in science or engineering fields," [...] and to be [...] "well qualified to manage the civilian research and development programs of the Department." ...|$|R
